com.pb.sawdust.util.format

Class DelimitedDataFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.format.DelimitedDataFormat

  • public class DelimitedDataFormat
extends java.lang.Object
    The DelimitedDataFormat class allows delimited text data to be produced in a systematic fashion. Each instance is tied to a specific delimiter char or String, and arrays of data passed into the format(...) methods will return strings containing that data delimited by the instance's delimiter. The formatting rules are as follows:
    • Except for the first item, each item immediately follows the delimiter.
    • If an item contains the delimiter, the item will be encased in double quote symbols (").
    • If an item contains double quotes, the item will be encased in double quote symbols amd its double quotes are replaced with "double-double quotes" ("").
    These rules are the producer-equivalent version of those described in DelimitedDataParser. This class also allows the formatting of the individual data items to be controlled through the use of formatters.

      • format

        public java.lang.String format(TextFormat[] formats,
                      java.lang.Object... data)
        Format a series of data items into a delimited data string using specified formats for each data item.
        Parameters:
        formats - The formats to use to convert each item in data into a string. Each item in this arry corresponds to the item in data with the same index.
        data - The data which will be formatted into a delimited text string.
        Returns:
        data as delimited text.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if formats.length != data.length or if a given item in data cannot be formatted with the corresponding format in formats.

      • format

        public java.lang.String format(java.lang.String[] formats,
                      java.lang.Object... data)
        Format a series of data items into a delimited data string using specified formats for each data item.
        Parameters:
        formats - The formats to use to convert each item in data into a string. Each item in this arry corresponds to the item in data with the same index. Each format must be a valid format for a single argument; i.e., it must contain only one '%' character (not including double percents ("%%') used for literal percent signs).
        data - The data which will be formatted into a delimited text string.
        Returns:
        data as delimited text.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if formats.length != data.length
        java.util.IllegalFormatException - if one of the formats in format have invalid syntax or cannot be used with the corresponding data item.

      • getFormatString

        public java.lang.String getFormatString(TextFormat... formats)
        Get a format string for delimited data using the specified formats. The returned string can be used as the format argument for a string format call (e.g. String.format(String,Object...). There will be one numbered argument for each format passed to this method.

        This method assumes that data formatted with the returned formatting string does not include the delimiter nor double quotes, or that they are already correctly escaped. To format data that does not satisfy this condition, use format(TextFormat[], Object...).

        Parameters:
        formats - The formats for the data.
        Returns:
        a delimited formatting string using formats.
